comments:
This reminded me how amazing it was for a 1982 adventure game, The Hobbit [1], to be able to parse longer and composite commands such as<p><pre><code>    SAY TO GANDALF &quot;GO EAST AND TAKE KEY AND GO SOUTHWEST.&quot;
</code></pre>
That was the first adventure game I had ever seen or played, and I remember being fascinated by the atmosphere driven by brief descriptions and simple graphics.<p>[1] <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;The_Hobbit_(1982_video_game)" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;en.wikipedia.org&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;The_Hobbit_(1982_video_game)</a>
